  "response_text": "A flat, graphic illustration opens on a wide, empty landscape: a tan desert-like plain stretches across the bottom, with a dark, low mountain ridge on the horizon and a bright blue sky above. Centered in large white capital letters is the title “THIS WEEK IN TV GUIDE.” The words sit over the landscape, bold and blocky, like a printed headline.\n\nA stylized television set begins to appear around the picture. Its screen has rounded corners and a thick, hand-drawn white and black border. The title remains briefly inside the TV screen, then disappears, leaving only the same desert horizon visible through the glass. The television itself is drawn as a boxy black cabinet with a white control panel along the top, including small dark rectangular controls and a small circular detail at one side. It stands alone in the flat tan landscape, facing forward, with the blue sky and distant dark hills still visible within its screen.\n\nThe image then becomes increasingly self-referential: the TV screen contains the same landscape, and within that landscape another smaller version of the same boxy television appears. The outer edges of a larger rounded TV screen frame surround the picture, so the viewer is looking at a television inside a television. The smaller set is centered inside the larger screen, with its own black cabinet, white top panel, and rounded screen showing the same desert horizon. The composition repeats for several moments, creating a nested effect of televisions receding inward, all against the simple blue-sky and tan-ground background.\n\nLater, the screen of the smaller inner television changes from the desert view to a dark blue-black surface with a few small white marks or symbols in the center. Almost immediately, a magazine cover begins to appear over the nested TV image. At first it is semi-transparent, then it becomes clearer and moves visually to the front. The cover is for TV Guide: a red box at the upper left contains the white words “TV GUIDE.” The rest of the cover has a pale yellow or beige background with an abstract illustration dominated by a large sweeping white and gray form, with smaller shapes and figures near the bottom.\n\nThe television imagery darkens behind the magazine until the TV Guide cover stands alone against a dark background. The magazine is upright and centered. Near the lower left, a circular black badge with a white outline appears, containing the words “ON SALE NOW” in white capital letters. The final image holds on the TV Guide cover and the “ON SALE NOW” badge, presenting the magazine as the visible product.",
